com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class RegisterCustomTableObjectRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.RegisterCustomTableObjectRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class RegisterCustomTableObjectRequest
extends SiperianRequest
    RegisterCustomTableObjectRequest is a request object to call Register Custom Table Object. You must register a custom stored procedure with Informatica MDM Hub in order to make it available to users in the Batch Group tool in the Hub Console. You can register the same custom job multiple times for different tables (in_rowid_table).

    Required Parameter:

    • setRowidTable(String) - Sets rowid table. Foreign key to c_repos_table.rowid_table. When the Hub Server calls the custom job in a batch group, this value is passed in.
    • setObjFuncTypeCode(String) - Sets Job type code. Must be 'A' for batch group custom jobs.
    • setObjFuncTypeDesc(String) - Sets display name for the custom batch job in the Batch Groups tool in the Hub Console.
    • setObjectName(String) - Sets package.procedure name of the custom job.

    Usage Example: 

    
 SiperianClient sipClient = SiperianClient.newSiperianClient(new File( context.getTestPTTStartDir() + "siperian-client.properties" ) );
 RegisterCustomTableObjectRequest req = new RegisterCustomTableObjectRequest();
 req.setRowidTable(jobContext.getRowIdTable());        // rowid table. e.g. SVR1.44A
 req.setObjFuncTypeCode("A");
 req.setObjFuncTypeDesc("Custom call");
 req.setObjectName("CMXBG.EXAMPLE_JOB");
 RegisterCustomTableObjectResponse executed = (RegisterCustomTableObjectResponse) sipClient.process( req );
 String errMessage = executed.getMessage();
 int rc = executed.getRetCode();

    See Also:

    API Pair: RegisterCustomTableObjectResponse

    API Group: Job Groups
